Command Line Lesson plan:
Commands Reference: https://www.git-tower.com/blog/posts/command-line-cheat-sheet

1. Indentify directory and files
pwd - print working directory
ls - list files and directories

2. navigate directories
cd - change directory

3. Exercise: Navigate through directories

4. Create Files and Directories
touch - create a file
mkdir - create a directory

5. Remove Files/Directories
rm - remove a file or directory

6. Copy/Move files
cp - copy a file
mv - move a file

7. Observe Files
head - view the first rows of a file
tail - view the last rows of a file
cat - view the entire file all at once
less - view the files by scrolling through it

8. Find Files
find - find a file

9. Grep Files
grep - find a pattern in a file

10. Pipes
| - combine (chain) commands

11. Command Substitution
$() - use the result of a command as a variable

12. Permissions
chmod
-https://help.ubuntu.com/community/FilePermissions
-chmod permission number explanations: https://www.linux.org/threads/file-permissions-chmod.4124/


-----------------------------------------
TEXT EDITOR: vim
(http://www.openvim.com/)

1. Open Text Editor
vim

2. Insert mode to add new text
i

3. Exit vim
press Esc
press Shift and :
:q!  -to quit without saving
:wq  -to quit and save

-----------------------------------------
GITHUB

1. Clone GitHub Account
git clone url - copy the files of a git repo locally
e.g. git clone https://github.com/Alexjmsherman/nlp_practicum_cohort1

2. Connect to remote repository
git remote add upstream url
e.g. git remote add upstream https://github.com/Alexjmsherman/nlp_practicum_cohort1.git